          "Logan Boese"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "In life, you were born and raised on the streets of El Paso, and were on the streets quite often, and fell in line with the wrong crowd. You got involved with some rough types, some bad types, some \"run-the-border-and-do-illegal-things\" types. One thing lead to another and you've basically been a career criminal ever since. If you've ever got a real job, it's only been temporary, and with a purpose or goal in mind. Your family wasn't much of an issue, and frankly, you felt all of you were better off without each other. You were dual language almost from birth, and you were good at following instructions, and better at remembering what you saw. You drifted across the border pretty often back in the day, and working for worse and worse types of people. When things went south one night, and one of them revealed a pair of fangs to you, you were surprised, but found after you woke up, that not much had changed. You did the job, and you got paid, though now you often took payment in blood. The bosses still treated you like shit, especially when they found out that you were what they called a \"Pander\", one of the clanless. An outcast with only other outcasts to watch your back. You worked for years, recognizing that only your usefulness and loyalty kept your own blood in your veins and they're fangs out of your neck. But all that changed recently, when you saw an opportunity and you took it, siding with the Camarilla in their push into Mexico City. Now, recognizing your talents, they've sent you out as one of the ones to spread the good word. You know it's probably because they consider you expendable, but you don't really care anymore. You're good at surviving and getting away."
        ],
